    "narrative": "For April 22, the lineup is anchored by **Will Smith** (72.68) and **Tyler Freeman** (71.80), who represent our highest-upside plays. **Will Smith** benefits from a potent combination of a 4.62 xERA matchup and favorable wind conditions, while **Tyler Freeman** is a priority start due to a massive 14% park adjustment and the exploitable pace of Buehler, which keeps our stolen base aggressive mandate front-and-center. Similarly, **Gleyber Torres** (67.52) and **Wenceel Perez** (66.93) are mandatory starts today; both benefit significantly from the +19% SP skill advantage against DL Hall, maximizing their efficiency in the 5x5 categories.\n\nThe most difficult decision today involved the marginal range, specifically the choice to leave **Luis Arraez** (46.87) on the bench. While **Luis Arraez** offers a stable floor, his matchup against Ohtani suppresses his ceiling to the point that **Jeremiah Jackson** (59.42) and **Daulton Varsho** (58.71) were favored for their higher overall scoring profiles and better platoon alignment. We are exercising caution with **Geraldo Perdomo** (49.00) and **Matt Chapman** (48.51); both are facing an elite arm in Ohtani and Kay, respectively, but remain active because our current roster depth necessitates their presence. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given the elite pitching matchups across the slate. We are keeping a close watch on **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (54.07); although his base projection is high, the matchup against a 3.27 xERA arm drags down his efficiency enough that he is performing closer to our secondary hitters today. Bench depth pieces like **Lawrence Butler**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Drew Gilbert** remain ready, but given the 40-point efficiency floor, they did not merit a start in a day where high-scoring matchups against weaker arms were available for the primary lineup.",
